  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "According to material classification, there are also metal bearings, non-metallic bearings, and porous metal bearings.",
    "The application of AI technology in bearing condition monitoring, performance prediction, design optimization, and other aspects is very extensive, mainly including: (1) predicting bearing lubrication status [300][301][302][303], friction coefficient [304], and wear rate [305];(2) identifying the wear mechanism of bearings [306] and optimize their design [307][308][309][310]; and (3) monitoring the service status of bearings using multiple signals [311][312][313][314][315][316].",
    "For example, Mokhtari et al. [317] extracted effective features in the time and frequency domains of acoustic emission signals, and used continuous wavelet transform and support vector machine to classify the dry friction, mixed friction, and fluid friction states of sliding bearings.",
    "Badawi et al. [307] applied artificial neural networks and fuzzy logic techniques to predict the performance of sliding bearings, based on performance characteristics such as bearing capacity, attitude angle, and maximum film pressure ratio under different aspect ratios.",
    "Other componentsThe application of AI in the research of other tribological components is relatively scattered, such as hydraulic transmission systems [318], automotive tires [319][320][321], pistons [322], bottom pivots [323], ball screws [324], and cam [325]."
  ],
